# mongodb-upgrade-research.conv - Research MongoDB 5.x upgrade compatibility
# Run: sdqctl iterate workflows/mongodb-upgrade-research.conv -n 5

MODEL claude-sonnet-4
ADAPTER copilot
MODE reporter
VALIDATION-MODE lenient


CONTEXT-LIMIT 60%

ELIDE
PROMPT We are writing a report researching MongoDB 5.x upgrade compatibility
for Nightscout cgm-remote-monitor.
ELIDE
PROMPT Discovery:
  docs/backlogs/README.md
  docs/backlogs/mongodb-upgrade-report.md
  1. Read docs/backlogs/mongodb-upgrade-report.md for work items
  2. Find items marked "📋 Ready"
  3. For this iteration, select a small to moderate related work items and plan
  what research and development will be needed.  Choose tightly scoped enough
  that we can be confident in the accuracy after teammates iteratively go
  through the whole list; just enough for this iteration.


PROMPT Research process:
  As appropriate for the selected work item, research to verify the accuracy in the report:
  - Track A (report-a*): Analyze client source in externals/
  - Track B (report-b*): Compare worktree vs baseline commits
  - Track C (report-c*): Test shape handling or document v3 behavior
  Update the report as appropriate based on the research we can accomplish.


PROMPT Source locations:
  - Worktree: /home/bewest/src/worktrees/nightscout/cgm-pr-8447
  - Baseline: externals/cgm-remote-monitor-official (tags: 14.2.5, 15.0.4)
  - Clients: externals/NightscoutKit, externals/AndroidAPS, externals/Trio-dev, externals/xDrip
ELIDE
PROMPT Deliverable per iteration:
  Update the report as appropriate based on the research.
  1. Fill in row of the relevant matrix in mongodb-upgrade-report.md
  2. Add code citations (file:line)
  3. Update work item status: 📋 Ready → ✅ Complete
  Ensure that the report is accurate and all claims we are adding can be verified.

OUTPUT-FORMAT markdown
